name: nytimes
text:
RT @elizabethjdias: Judge Amy Coney Barrett is regarded as, at least for now, the leading contender to replace RBG. For anti-abortion activists, she is pretty much "perfect."

name: nytimes
text:
The coronavirus crisis in the U.S. has claimed nearly 200,000 lives. 

For those who’ve lost loved ones, everywhere they turn is a reminder of their pain as they are left to grieve in a country still firmly gripped by the pandemic. https://t.co/acrtFg3ASA

name: nytimes
text: Jimmy Kimmel delivered what for viewers at home looked and sounded like a normal Emmys monologue, with pauses for applause and cuts to a star-studded audience. But the crowd reactions were from past awards shows. https://t.co/yvGhmx2lD2

name: nytimes
text:

text: RT @nytimesarts: Damon Lindelof and Cord Jefferson win best writing for a limited series for “Watchmen” at the #Emmys. Jefferson referenced the Tulsa Race Massacre, which the show depicted. Here's what you should know about it. https://t.co/UDgEiMb8QF

name: nytimes
text:
Judge Amy Coney Barrett is regarded — at least for now — as the leading contender to replace Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg. If nominated and confirmed, she would be viewed as a home run by conservative Christians and anti-abortion activists.

text: The story of President Trump and CNN's president, Jeff Zucker — who put “The Apprentice” on NBC and made Trump a household name — is a Frankenstein tale for the late television age, about a TV executive who lost control of his creation, writes @benyt. https://t.co/mx60BfBLQL
